As of the 2010 census, there were 37 people living in the CDP: 16 male and 21 female. 17 were 19 years old or younger, 6 were ages 20–34, 2 were between the ages of 35 and 49, 3 were between 50 and 64, and the remaining 9 were aged 65 and above. The median age was 25.5 years.

The racial makeup of the CDP was 95% [[Native Americans in the United States|American Indian]], and 5% [[White Americans|White]]. 8% of the population were [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] of any race.

There were 13 households in the CDP, nine family households (69%) and four non-family households (31%), with an average household size of 2.9. Of the family households, two were married couples living together, while there were one single father and six single mothers; the non-family households included four adults living alone: three male and one female.

The CDP contained 15 housing units, of which 13 were occupied and two were vacant.<ref name=GR2>{{cite web |url=https://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/10_DP/DPDP1/1600000US0449710 |title=American FactFinder: Nolic CDP, Arizona |publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]] |access-date=January 2, 2017 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://archive.today/20200213110042/https://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/10_DP/DPDP1/1600000US0449710 |archive-date=February 13, 2020 }}</ref>

